title: Cedar and Oak co-housing room avaliable!
posting_body: ['Hello!', "Cedar and Oak is a predominantly queer co-housing (aspiring cooperative) house in Seattle's Wedgwood neighborhood.", 'We are looking for a long term housemate for one of our rooms!', "The Space/Situation: We're an 8 person (and 2 cat) home in Wedgwood near the Safeway on 35th/75th .", "We've got large living spaces, a big overgrown project garden, wood fireplaces and a sauna (currently stove-less)  in the backyard.", 'We buy house supplies as a group.', 'In addition, house members commit to spending at least 2 hours a week working on house projects (groceries, cleaning, fixes, gardening, grandiose construction schemes), and attending biweekly house meetings to keep it all together.', "About us: we're a smorgasbord mixture of students, teachers, bodyworkers, artists, activists and professionals who share a commitment for living together intentionally.", 'The room is an upstairs room with a view overlooking the backyard and large oak tree, it has wood flooring and a closet, and is $625/mo.', 'Rent includes $25 for group housing supplies/consumables.', 'Utilities are not included but typically run $30/mo for power, and $50/mo for water/sewer/garbage on a 3 month bill cycle.', 'Internet is $10 (gigabit, wi-fi, might be possible to provide a Ethernet line if needed).', 'Street parking is ample, and a new bus stop was added in just down the corner.', 'Who you are: We are looking for people happy to participate in the house and community.', 'We like to hang out, share meals occasionally, invite friends over, do art or play music, and also get those house chores done!', "Recognizing that we offer a very attractive and affordable housing option in Seattle, we strongly encourage prospective house members who are BIPOC, are queer or trans, or who may otherwise be discriminated in Seattle's housing process.", 'How to Reply: Please reply through craigslist telling us about yourself.', 'It really stands out if you can send in a message with a paragraph or two about yourself, what your situation is, etc etc.', 'Some ideas to include: your interests, your previous experience with community living if any, what you do for work or for fun perhaps.', 'If you identify as a person of color, queer or trans, please include that if you feel comfortable.', "The Process: Based on your response, we'll schedule one to two meetings for you to see the space and meet with everyone in the house, and then make decisions as a house.", 'We aim to get a final response to you within 2 weeks from the final meeting, though it may be sooner.', 'Credit to the Sherwood Coop, this advertisement was adapted from their excellent one.']
